class="entry-text"><p>On desktop devices, the larger screen size allows the high-quality images to shine and works especially well with the before and after photos. One thing we did notice is that the top menu disappears when scrolling, which seems like an oversite since it appears on the mobile version. Overall, the desktop site loaded quickly and is easy to navigate. It scored 71/100 for performance on Google's PageSpeed Insights test.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-zack-of-all-trades-20240522-mobile.webp"
